Mouthparts. Buccal cone elongated. Labrum pointed, with ventral sclerifications ogival. Labrum chaetotaxy with 0/2,2 smooth chaetae of different sizes, prelabral chaetae absent. Labium with 11 chaetae: a1, a2, p2, E, F, G, b, c, d, e and f. Labial papillae x not detected. Maxilla styliform (
Fig. 19
), mandible thin with four teeth, being two basal stronger, unequal teeth and two smaller, subequal apical teeth (
Fig. 18
).

Ventral chaetotaxy. On head, groups Vea, Vem and Vep with 4, 3, 3−4 chaetae, respectively; group Vi with 6 chaetae (
Fig. 23
). On Abd IV, furcal vestige with 5−6 chaetae, devoid of mi but with a small posterior area of primary granulation. Ventral chaetae Vl and L' on Abd V present (
Fig. 20
).
